rip-only(1) -- remove RubyGems from the current ripenv
======================================================

## SYNOPSIS

`rip-only` [-d]

## DESCRIPTION

`rip-only` isolates the current ripenv by disabling or removing
RubyGems. To add RubyGems back, use the `-d` flag.

## EXAMPLES

  $ ruby -rubygems -e 'Gem'
  $ rip-only
  $ ruby -rubygems -e 'Gem'
  -e:1: uninitialized constant Gem (NameError)

